  "texts": [
    "foot_1 Specifically, the NPMI score between two words (x i, x j) is calculated as follows:",
    "It computes the normalized mutual information of two words, and then takes the average of all word pairs in all topics.",
    "Here is to avoid zero; p(x i) is the probability of word x i, and p(x i, x j) is the co-occurrence probability of (x i, x j).",
    "These probabilities are estimated as their occurrence frequencies in a reference corpus.",
    "The reference corpus can be either internal (the training set) or external (e.g., Wikipedia articles)."
  ],
